panels.name: All Actions Over Time
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=corp/security/umbrella (Allowed or Blocked)
| parse "\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\"" as Timestamp,Most_Granular_Identity,Identities,InternalIp,ExternalIp,Action,QueryType,ResponseCode,Domain,Categories
// Geo Lookup
| where action matches "Allowed" or action matches "Blocked"
| lookup latitude, longitude, country_code, country_name, region, city, postal_code from geo://location on ip = ExternalIp
// count by action and time
| timeslice 1h
| count by _timeslice, action
| transpose row _timeslice column action

children.name: Cisco Umbrella DNS Logs Parser
children.description: Based on Cisco umbrella documentation here: https://support.umbrella.com/hc/en-us/articles/231248508-Log-Management-Export-Format-and-Versioning

panels.name: Blocked Categories
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=corp/security/umbrella Blocked
| parse "\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\"" as timestamp, granular_id, ids, internal_ip, external_ip, action, query_type, response_code, domain, categories
| where action = "Blocked"
| where !isEmpty(categories)
| count categories
| sort _count
| limit 50

panels.name: DNS to File Sharing Category
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=corp/security/umbrella
| parse "\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\"" as Timestamp,Most_Granular_Identity,Identities,InternalIp,ExternalIp,Action,QueryType,ResponseCode,Domain,Categories

| count by timestamp, action, domain, categories, internalip, most_granular_identity
| sort by timestamp

panels.name: Unique DNS Requests (Ascending)
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=corp/security/umbrella
| parse "\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\"" as Timestamp,Most_Granular_Identity,Identities,InternalIp,ExternalIp,Action,QueryType,ResponseCode,Domain,Categories
| where Most_Granular_Identity != "*Guest*"
| where !(responsecode matches "NXDOMAIN")
|count by action, domain
| sort by _count asc

panels.name: *<your_domain>.com Spoofing WIP
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=corp/security/umbrella
| parse "\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\"" as Timestamp,Most_Granular_Identity,Identities,InternalIp,ExternalIp,Action,QueryType,ResponseCode,Domain,Categories
| where (domain matches "<your_domain>.com*.") OR (domain matches "*<your_domain>*.")
| count by action, domain
| sort by _count asc

panels.name: Hyphenated Domains
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=corp/security/umbrella
| parse "\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\"" as Timestamp,Most_Granular_Identity,Identities,InternalIp,ExternalIp,Action,QueryType,ResponseCode,Domain,Categories

| count by action, domain, most_granular_identity
| sort by _count
| sort by _count asc

panels.name: Unresolved DNS Queries
panels.queryString:
_sourceCategory=corp/security/umbrella
| parse "\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\",\"*\"" as Timestamp,Most_Granular_Identity,Identities,InternalIp,ExternalIp,Action,QueryType,ResponseCode,Domain,Categories
| where isEmpty(categories)
| where responsecode matches "NXDOMAIN"
//| where domain matches "*cbcbcbcb.com*"
| where !(domain matches "local.") OR !(domain matches "local.") OR !(domain matches "co2*.")
| count by domain, most_granular_identity, internalip
| sort by _count
